<h1>Quote Declined</h1>

<p>
    {{customerName}} has declined quote #{{quoteNumber}}.
</p>

<div class="info-box" style="background-color: #fee2e2; border-left-color: #dc2626;">
    <h3>‚ùå Quote Rejected</h3>
    <p style="color: #991b1b;">
        The customer has decided not to proceed at this time.
    </p>
</div>

<div class="info-box">
    <h3>Quote Details</h3>
    <p><strong>Quote Number:</strong> {{quoteNumber}}</p>
    <p><strong>Total Amount:</strong> {{formatCurrency quoteTotal "CAD"}}</p>
    <p><strong>Customer:</strong> {{customerName}}</p>
    <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:{{customerEmail}}">{{customerEmail}}</a></p>
</div>

{{#if rejectionReason}}
<div class="info-box">
    <h3>Rejection Reason</h3>
    <p>{{rejectionReason}}</p>
</div>
{{/if}}

<h2>Recommended Follow-Up Actions</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Review the quote</strong> to understand if pricing or scope was a concern</li>
    <li><strong>Reach out to the customer</strong> to understand their decision better</li>
    <li><strong>Offer to revise the quote</strong> if there are concerns you can address</li>
    <li><strong>Keep them in your pipeline</strong> for future opportunities</li>
    <li><strong>Request feedback</strong> to improve future quotes</li>
</ul>

<h2>Quick Actions</h2>

{{> button text="View Quote in Dashboard" url=dashboardUrl}}

<div style="margin-top: 20px;">
    <a href="mailto:{{customerEmail}}" style="color: #2563eb; text-decoration: none; margin-right: 20px;">üìß Email Customer</a>
</div>

<div class="divider"></div>

<p style="font-size: 14px; color: #6b7280;">
    <strong>Tip:</strong> A polite follow-up email can help you understand the customer's concerns and potentially save the deal.
</p>